Rapper Jude Lemfani Abaga aka MI Abaga has hinted on an incoming album, which will attract global recognition. Mr Incredible, who recently announced his engagement to beau, Eniola Mafe, took to his Twitter page to ask fans to anticipate his next body of work.   Personal errors, not devil destroy marriage – Daddy…     I don’t joke when in my CEO mode – Olamide…     Tiwa Savage sells out tickets for ‘Water &…   According to him, he can now focus on making a ‘classic’ album which is likely to earn him an award at the Grammys. He tweeted: “And now that that is all over… music coming soon. Now I can focus so I release this album properly.. because it is a classic. Might win a Grammy.. I appreciate your patience”. MI’s last album, “A Study on Self Worth: Yxng Dxnzl” was released in August 2018 and got nominated for the Best Rap Album at the 2019 Headies Award show.